 has already agreed, and this is a bit contradictory, I think the safer interpretation is: the customer does NOT actually want to cancel the grill. The parenthetical note is telling me their true preference - they want to keep it.\n\n\nThe parenthetical clarifies their actual preference—they'd decline if asked to confirm. Since the instructions assume prior agreement but this note explicitly contradicts that, I should respect what they'd actually choose and keep the grill. I'll provide the t-shirt material details instead.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1885,"cache_read_input_tokens":25947,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1885},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZEDAXADVqKQr8MtnVSnp","type":"assistant","uuid":"9173aa69-ce98-46fb-8025-67898a945190","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:56:04.037Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/Users/shiladityabanerjee/Projects/tau2-mermaid","sessionId":"6ea121f6-72d9-4799-b679-aedd953592a7","version":"2.1.80","gitBranch":"main"}
